"content_id": "2221",
"reference_id": 0,
"version": "1.0.2",
"title": "2221: Jesus Christ, Son of Man",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2221: jesus christ, son of man",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ's preferred title for himself. The term points to the humanity and servanthood of Christ, but also reflects Daniel's vision of the son of man as a coming figure of judgment and authority.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of Man in his human nature</h2>\n<h3>OT use of <code>son of man'' to mean</code>human being''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:6\">JOB 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:8\">JOB 35:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:4\">PSA 8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:17\">PSA 80:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:3\">PSA 144:3</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ describes himself as Son of Man to stress his humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:20\">MAT 8:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:58\">LUK 9:58</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:19\">MAT 11:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:34\">LUK 7:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:13\">MAT 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:15\">MAT 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:22\">LUK 6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:35\">JHN 9:35</a></p>\n<h3>Blasphemy against the Son of Man is forgivable</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:32\">MAT 12:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:10\">LUK 12:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of Man in his prophetic ministry</h2>\n<h3>The OT use of ``son of man'' as a title for Ezekiel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:1\">EZK 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ preaches God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:37-Matt13:43\">MAT 13:37–13:43</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ offers the words of eternal life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:27\">JHN 6:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:53\">JHN 6:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:68\">JHN 6:68</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of Man in his suffering and death</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as a servant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ came to suffer, die and be raised</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:6-Luke24:7\">LUK 24:6–24:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:40\">MAT 12:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:30\">LUK 11:30</a> <em>the sign of Jonah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:9\">MAT 17:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:9\">MRK 9:9</a> <em>the transfiguration</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:22-Matt17:23\">MAT 17:22–17:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:31\">MRK 9:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:44\">LUK 9:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18\">MAT 20:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33\">MRK 10:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31\">LUK 18:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:24\">MAT 26:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:21\">MRK 14:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:22\">LUK 22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:14\">JHN 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:23\">JHN 12:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:31\">JHN 13:31</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the Son of Man in his authority and dominion</h2>\n<h3>The vision of the son of man</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a></strong> <em>This passage provides the main OT background to Jesus Christ's understanding of himself as the “Son of Man”. His main uses of the title emphasise his dominion and authority, and also paradoxically that this glory will be attained through the humiliation of the cross.</em></p>\n<h3>Son of man meaning ``son of Adam''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26\">GEN 1:26</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ as Son of Man (in the Hebrew “son of Adam”) inherits the promise originally given to Adam of dominion over creation, which Adam forfeited because of his fall into sin.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:14\">ROM 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:45\">1CO 15:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:6-Heb2:9\">HEB 2:6–2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:4-Ps8:6\">PSA 8:4–8:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ had authority on earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:6\">MAT 9:6</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:10\">MRK 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:24\">LUK 5:24</a> <em>Authority to forgive sins.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:8\">MAT 12:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:28\">MRK 2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:5\">LUK 6:5</a> <em>authority over the Sabbath</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is now ascended into glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55-Acts7:56\">ACT 7:55–7:56</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:13\">REV 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:14\">REV 14:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ will come to judge and reign over all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27-Matt16:28\">MAT 16:27–16:28</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:26\">LUK 9:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:23\">MAT 10:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30\">MAT 24:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26\">MRK 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27\">LUK 21:27</a> <em>the second coming</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:44\">MAT 24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:40\">LUK 12:40</a> <em>the day and hour unknown</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:64\">MAT 26:64</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:62\">MRK 14:62</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:69\">LUK 22:69</a> <em>Jesus Christ before the Sanhedrin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:8\">LUK 18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:36\">LUK 21:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a></p>",
